# 007 — Light sources & illumination (Part E)

## Spec reference

- `C:\GitHub\Berreman\specs\0022\.spec-md` — parent spec (Spec 0022).
- Slice 001 (`.slices/001.slice-md`) — created the `OpticalConstructor.*` projects and fixed the buildable FuncUI interpretation this slice relies on.
- Slice 002 (`.slices/002.slice-md`) — domain foundation: `Units.fs` (`UnitOfMeasure` + boundary conversions), the beam tree, and the `OpticalConstructorProject` aggregate + `$defs` anchors this slice extends.

## Inherited from parent spec

### Binding constraints (from `.spec-md` ## 0)

The following constraints are normative for EVERY part (A–J) of this specification. A directive in any later part that conflicts with one of these is void.

1. **Platform & language commitment.** The solution MUST target **.NET 10** and MUST be **F#-first** end to end: engine, orchestration, UI, and tooling are all F#. The domain model MUST be expressed as F# records and discriminated unions. C# projects are admitted ONLY where they already exist in the Berreman tree as cloned dependencies (`../MathNetNumerics/Numerics/Numerics.csproj`, cited at `C:/GitHub/Berreman/Berreman/Berreman.slnx:8`). No part MAY introduce a new C# project.

2. **Reuse before invention.** Every directive that touches an area already served by a Berreman primitive MUST name and call that primitive rather than re-implementing it, and MUST cite it as `<file>:<symbol>` or `<file>:<line>`. New modules, files, or abstractions are admitted ONLY when they trace to a named directive in this spec; a new artefact with no such trace MUST be dropped. The 4×4 solver (`Solvers.fs` `OpticalSystemSolver`), the field model (`Fields.fs` `EmFieldSystem`), the tensor model (`MaterialProperties.fs` `OpticalProperties`), and the units constants (`Constants.fs`) MUST NOT be forked, re-derived, or shadowed.

3. **Canonical-units rule.** All physical quantities MUST be stored internally in the single canonical SI base already used by the engine — **meters** for length/thickness, with `WaveLength` reduced to meters via its `.value` member (`Fields.fs:284`). Conversion to and from any human-facing unit (nm, µm/mkm, Å, mm, eV, cm⁻¹) MUST happen ONLY at the UI/IO boundary. No part MAY store a non-SI unit in the domain model, a project JSON payload, or a `.binz` pickle.

4. **JSON-canonical / `.binz`-derived rule.** The canonical, hand/LLM-editable project definition MUST be JSON, validated against a published JSON Schema on load. Zipped FsPickler (`.binz`, via `Softellect.Sys.Core.serialize`/`BinaryZippedFormat`, `Core.fs:257`) MUST be used ONLY for derived/bulk artefacts (sweeps, field maps, fit histories, caches) referenced as sidecars from the JSON; it MUST NOT carry the canonical project definition. No part MAY serialize the domain project model with FsPickler.

5. **FuncUI audit gate.** The Avalonia.FuncUI clone at `C:\GitHub\Avalonia.FuncUI.Clone\` MUST pass the mandatory audit (defined in §A.9) and be cleared of all flagged content BEFORE it is linked. No part MAY reference, link, or build against the clone until the audit passes. The clone's linking mechanism (local NuGet package OR project reference) is deliberately undecided and MUST remain undecided until that decision is taken later — no part MAY resolve it.

6. **Minimum implementation.** Each part SHALL deliver the minimum that satisfies its directives. Caching, retries, added abstraction layers, config knobs, schema versioning, error-wrapping shims, backwards-compatibility shims, and migration code are OUT OF SCOPE unless a named directive in the owning part puts them in scope.

7. **Tier fidelity.** Every feature carried from 010 MUST keep its `[Core]`/`[Standard]` label. No part MAY retier, silently drop, or invent a feature absent from both 010 and the Berreman tree.

### Acceptance criteria owned by this slice

- AC-E1: After the operator enters wavelength, incidence angle, polarization, and ellipticity in the Source editor and commits, `SourceSpec.toIncidentLight` MUST return an `IncidentLightInfo` (Fields.fs:338) whose `waveLength.value` equals the entered wavelength converted to meters and whose polarization/ellipticity/angle match the inputs, within one recompute cycle.
- AC-E2: After choosing a non-nm/µm display unit (Å, mm, eV, or cm⁻¹) for wavelength, the produced `WaveLength` (Fields.fs:280) MUST carry the value converted via the §A.10 boundary conversions and the domain model MUST store no non-SI unit, verified on save of the project JSON.
- AC-E3: After toggling a wavelength or angle input to Ranged, the Source editor MUST produce a `RangedVariable` (Variables.fs:42) of the matching case (WaveLengthRange/IncidenceAngleRange) handed unchanged to the sweep layer, with no new range type introduced.
- AC-E4: After selecting the RCP, LCP, or unpolarized preset in the Poincaré/ellipse picker, the source MUST set Ellipticity ±1.0 (clamped via Ellipticity.create, Fields.fs:306) for RCP/LCP or Coherence.Unpolarized for unpolarized, and the live Stokes readout MUST be computed via EmField.stokesVector (FieldFunctions.fs:44).
- AC-E5: After attaching a SpectralProfile (Blackbody/D65/A/LaserLine/Imported) and a wavelength range, `SpectralProfile.sample` MUST return a list of (WaveLength, weight) pairs in canonical meters, one `IncidentLightInfo` per sample, with imported spectra read from a sidecar via FSharp.Data and not from a project `.binz`.
- AC-E6: After setting a ConeAcceptance with N samples, `ConeAcceptance.sample` MUST fan the base incidence angle into N weighted sub-angles and the combined result MUST be averaged on Stokes/intensity outputs (FieldFunctions.fs:44,69), not on field amplitudes; a collimated source MUST be represented by `cone = None`.
- AC-E7: After setting coherence to Incoherent, the source MUST be solved through the existing substrate-driven Multiple/MultipleEmFieldSystem path (Solvers.fs:152, Fields.fs:571) with no separate incoherent solver added; Unpolarized MUST be evaluated as the incoherent average of Polarization.s and Polarization.p (Fields.fs:322,323).
- AC-E8: After defining multiple SourceSpec values in `project.sources`, the combined illumination MUST be a weighted incoherent StokesVector sum (Fields.fs:584,586) of every expanded `IncidentLightInfo`, with no field-level summation across sources and no cached expansion list.
- AC-E9: After enabling a GaussianBeamSpec, `GaussianBeamSpec.angularSpectrum` MUST decompose the beam into weighted plane-wave incidence angles using the existing createGaussian (FourierTransform.fs:74) and FourierTransform (FourierTransform.fs:137), introducing no new FFT or Gaussian generator.
- AC-E10: After opening the element palette, the operator MUST be able to add a `ConstructorElement.Source` and open its editor in one click with no confirmation gate, and the Source panel MUST be reachable from the palette navigation.

