## Testing plan

Gates: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests` (all three).

- `constructor-unit-tests` gate runs the new `OpticalConstructor.Tests` files; must pass and increase the count over the prior slice's baseline.
- AC-E1/AC-E2 (`SourceProjectionTests.fs`): `SourceSpec.toIncidentLight` round-trips — `waveLength.value` equals the entered wavelength converted to meters, polarization/ellipticity/angle equal inputs; Å/mm/eV/cm⁻¹ display units land on `WaveLength.Nm`/`WaveLength.Mkm` via the §A.10 boundary conversions with no non-SI unit stored.
- AC-E5..AC-E9 (`SourceExpansionTests.fs`): `SpectralProfile.sample`, `ConeAcceptance.sample`, `Unpolarized`, and `GaussianBeamSpec.angularSpectrum` expand into the expected weighted `IncidentLightInfo` lists; `SourceCombination` sums `StokesVector` via `Fields.fs:584,586` with no field-level summation across sources; imported spectra read from a sidecar via FSharp.Data, not a `.binz`.
- AC-E3: a Ranged toggle yields a `RangedVariable` of the matching case (`WaveLengthRange`/`IncidenceAngleRange`) handed unchanged to the sweep layer, no new range type.
- AC-E4: RCP/LCP set `Ellipticity.create ±1.0`, unpolarized sets `Coherence.Unpolarized`, live Stokes readout via `EmField.stokesVector` (`FieldFunctions.fs:44`).
- AC-E6: collimated represented by `cone = None`; cone averaging on Stokes/intensity (`FieldFunctions.fs:44,69`), not on field amplitudes.
- AC-E7: `Incoherent` routes through the substrate-driven `Multiple`/`MultipleEmFieldSystem` path (`Solvers.fs:152`, `Fields.fs:571`), no separate incoherent solver.
- AC-E8: `project.sources` combined illumination is a weighted incoherent `StokesVector` sum, no cached expansion list.
- AC-E10: palette discoverability — one-click add of `ConstructorElement.Source` and open its editor with no confirmation gate (asserted at the UI/model seam without an Avalonia type).
- `build` gate green at Release/x64; `unit-tests` gate (BerremanTests) stays green (not touched here).

## Risks

- **Medium.** The expand-on-the-boundary discipline is the load-bearing contract: spectral profiles, cones, unpolarized, and multi-source averaging MUST all fan a base `IncidentLightInfo` into weighted `IncidentLightInfo` values and average on `StokesVector`/intensity OUTPUTS, never on `EmField` amplitudes — averaging on fields would silently break the physics. Mitigation: prove the expansion/averaging seams by unit test before exit, and keep `SourceSpec` wrapping exactly one `IncidentLightInfo` with no duplicated fields. The non-nm/µm wavelength path (Å/mm/eV/cm⁻¹ → `WaveLength.Nm`) must route through the slice-002 `Units.fs` `toWaveLength`, not a hand-rolled conversion. The picker's 3D Poincaré rendering must consume the reserved OpenTK viewport, not introduce a second renderer.
- **Low (UI).** FuncUI package resolution — the public MIT `Avalonia.FuncUI` NuGet (slice 001 interpretation), never the audit-gated clone. Keep `view` bodies pure functions of `SourceSpec` with no Avalonia type leaking into the model/`update`.

## Hand-off

The source/illumination layer exists and is unit-tested: `SourceSpec` + its DUs and pure expand/sample/angularSpectrum functions (`SourceSpec.fs`), the weighted incoherent reducer (`SourceCombination.fs`), the [Core] source editor and the bidirectional Poincaré/ellipse picker (`Sources/`), and the aggregate's `sources` field + `sourceSpec` `$def` shape. Part F (slice 008) consumes the `RangedVariable` values produced here through `calculate`/`calculate3D` and owns the sweep/chart/CIE wiring; Part J §J.12 (slice 016) delivers the OpenTK viewport the E.4 picker consumes. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
